   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Otosan Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ford Otomotiv Sanayi A.S. (Otosan or the Company) is a leading Turkish automotive manufacturer and exporter of commercial and passenger vehicles. The proposed IFC investment is up to EUR equivalent of US$150 million to partially fund Otosans capex program during the period of 2020-2024 including the launch of new commercial vehicle models, capacity expansion and other climate related investments such as (i) production of electric and hybrid cars; (ii) efficiency; and (iii) modernization and automation (the Project).</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Project&apos;s expected development includes: (i) economywide and employment effects; (ii) skills/know-how development via increased technical jobs and skills development, and (iii) promotion of sector integration via product and process innovation and increasing manufacturing complexity.</narrative>
  </description>
